g.text: 1st Battalion disembark at Havre. Part of the Expeditionary Force, 11th Infantry Brigade, 4th Division.
1st Battalion in action at Solesmes.
1st Battalion at Battle of Le Cateau.
1st Battalion in rear guard action at Nauroy.
2nd Battalion arrived at Bombay from Mhow.
1st Battalion in Retreat from Mons 11th Brigade, 4th Division.
After 11 days’ withdrawal from Le Cateau, 1st Battalion started to advance towards the River Aisne.
1st Battalion in Battle of the Marne.
1st Battalion at the Battle of the Aisne. 11th Brigade were first British troops to cross.
1st Battalion engaged at Bucy-le-Long.
1st Battalion left the River Aisne having been in action since 12th September.
Hampshire Territorial Brigade embarked with Wessex Division for India.
1st Battalion at Battle of Armentieres.
1st Battalion (11th Brigade) moved up to Courte Croix to reinforce 12th Brigade.
1st Battalion at Bailleul.
1st Battalion rushed Nieppe and carried Pont de Nieppe.
1st Battalion occupied Armentieres.
1st Battalion took up position at ‘Plug Street’ and here gained the name of ‘Stonewallers’.
1st Battalion holding front line trenches at St Ives.
1st Battalion engaged at Armentieres.

1st Bn left Cairo for Suez to embark for India.

1/4th Bn disembarked at Basra.
2nd Bn sailed from Avonmouth for the Dardanelles.
